    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-04-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5331/159</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Portuguese Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bianchi</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-04-14">April 14,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your Excellency’s note dated the
                    11th instant, enclosing the draft of a proposed <hi rend="italic"
                        >modus-vivendi</hi> to be concluded between our two Governments, to take the
                    place of the commercial arrangement effected by exchange of notes signed at
                    Washington on June 28, 1910.</p>
                <p>In your note, your Excellency was good enough to outline the general policy of
                    the United States Government in matters commercial and to express the hope that
                    it may be able, in harmony with such policy, to continue, as up to the present,
                    to apply the concessions granted to trade agreements to articles the growth,
                    produce or manufacture of Portugal.</p>
                <p>I am forwarding to my Government, without delay, the draft under acknowledgment
                    and shall not fail to inform your Excellency of their reply in due course.<note
                        n="5" xml:id="d350fn5">No further reply was received. The preliminary
                        discussions were renewed in 1938.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I avail myself [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bianchi</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
